cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CR, cs.SE, cs.DS

This paper is about a new classification tool that focuses on providing a formal foundation of decision trees to support logical analysis and verification of learned prediction models. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper introduces a Model Audit module that formally verifies the prediction model against user specifications, which suggests that it may also belong to the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) and Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses implementation details ranging from programming paradigm to memory management that help achieve high-performance computation, which suggests that it may also belong to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category.
